<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Native Americans probably burned this vegetation historically at different frequencies throughout the state. Although we know little about fire returns for this and other native annual vegetation types in cismontane California, seed banks and annual habit of the diagnostic species likely enable short fire return intervals (Reiner 2007, Wills 2006). Keeley (2002a) suggested that fires occurred in higher frequency adjacent to long-term occupation sites, and Anderson (2005) suggested that many annual plants and associated geophytes benefited from tending by Native Americans.</div>
